Introduction

Seungyeon (also known as Chang Seung Yeon) is a South Korean singer and dancer under Wild Entertainment Group. She is a former member of the girl group CLC.

She debuted as a member of CLC on March 19, 2015, with the group's first mini album "First Love".

On March 6, 2016, it was announced that CLC's leader role, originally held by Seunghee, would be passed onto Seungyeon.

On March 18, 2022, Seungyeon left Cube Entertainment after her exclusive contract concluded.

On February 8, 2023, Seungyeon announced that she had signed with Wild Entertainment Group as a solo artist.
